comm: starts off with a short ball on the rib cage, Khawaja hops across to nurdle it to fine leg
floats it full on middle, tails away a touch but Finch is well forward as he defends
gets some lift off the good length spot on off stump, bunted to cover
beaten by a peach of a delivery that holds its line after pitching on off. Finch, drawn forward, is squared up. That wasn't far away from the edge
on middle and leg, worked wide of midwicket for an easy single

tennis ball bounce on that occasion. This one's angled across at length, the ball takes off from one particular spot as Khawaja is hit on the glove as the ball lobs short of slip. The bottom hand was off the grip as he defended.
stays inside the crease and taps a short of length delivery to the off side

crunching cover drive. A simple extension of the arms as he plants his foot forward to meet the ball. Delightful to say the least, but there was nothing wrong with the delivery. Finch was hitting on the up
gets back into the crease and whips an incoming length ball to midwicket
pulls and misses. That was a real quick delivery, bowled at 142 clicks. Finch looks to play in front of square off the frontfoot but was late on the stroke
punched off the frontfoot to Pollard at cover

top shot! Half-volley outside off, Finch leans forward and uses his straight bat to loft cleanly over the infield. Didn't look like he intended to hit it over the ropes, but the ball nearly sailed over. Lands a yard or two inside the ropes
hops back and across to pat that back down the pitch
another short ball on middle, Khawaja wrists it to midwicket
imperious! Swivels, gets on top of the bounce and pulls it behind square. Getting into position early was the key, and he did just that. Too short from Holder on that occasion
this one's much better, floats it ahead of the good length area on off, the ball jags away a touch, Khawaja defends towards short cover

overcompensates by bowling it too full on off stump, Khawaja leans into the drive to essay that over cover point. Bounced over Pollard's head as it raced away. His head was super still as he made contact
nips one off the deck from outside off, Khawaja shoulders arms
gets half-forward and eases it towards Narine at mid-on and scampers through for a quick single
slants one across Khawaja, who drives it straight to Narine at mid-off
as good as it can get, delightful straight drive. Shows the full face of the bat to caress that past the bowler and mid-off
on the pads, whipped to deep midwicket
nudges this one from outside off towards deep backward square leg. Not much movement on that occasion
worked off his hip again towards deep square, easy picking those. Finch hopped across and used the depth of the crease to find the gap
hops across, opens the bat face and steers it to backward point
glides it to point where Fletcher slides to his right to stop what looked a certain single

poor shot selection has consumed him. Not much feet movement as Khawaja looks to cut, but the ball was a lot fuller than he would have liked, and the thin edge is pouched by Denesh Ramdin. Boundaries were reeling off the blade, so a timely wicket for West Indies. The skipper has struck and it seems there isn't much wrong with his hamstring going by his roaring celebration there.
shuffles across the stumps and flicks the buffet ball on middle and leg to the fine leg boundary. That wasn't an ideal delivery first up
shuffles across again, this time punches the length ball on middle to midwicket
hint of extra bounce from middle, Smith pushes outside the line and his hit on the elbow as the ball rolls to Ramdin. Ouch!
angles a full ball on off stump, pushed to cover
looks to pull but is late on the stroke, ball deflects off the thigh pad to Ramdin behind the stumps
worked off the pads to deep square leg, the fielder had to move a good 20 yards to his left to cut that off
punches the incoming length ball to mid-on
floats it at length on off stump, pushed to cover. Better lines and lengths in this over
plays outside the line, gets a thick inside edge to midwicket
holds onto the surface again as Smith awkwardly bunts it to the off side. The bat face turned in his hand as he defended
shuffles across to tap that short of length delivery on off towards point
gets half-forward to solidly defend that full delivery on off stump
excellent leave, in that zone outside off where most batsmen aren't sure whether to play forward or go back
driven firmly, but straight to mid-off
floats that on off stump, touch fuller than usual, Smith lets that go
length ball on middle and leg, worked to midwicket
too straight, and he's worked that wide of the diving midwicket fielder. Finch was in perfect balance as he used his wrists to pick the gap
no rhythm at all. Too short, and Finch will gobble those for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Hops back, uses the length to whip that away behind square on the leg side

straight as a dye, balance, timing, power all in sync as the ball made a sweet sound as it made contact with Finch's big broad blade. Uses a straight bat to loft him through the line, the ball dents the sightscreen on the full
didn't get hold of it, but it's still a boundary. Too full, Finch decides to go straight, but ends up dragging it a bit, clears mid-on though. Finch is slowly revving up his innings
this one's punched down the ground, straight to mid-on though. 16 off that
bunts that length ball to cover, calls no immediately
slower delivery, Smith opens the face of the bat late to steer that into the gap behind point, third man runs around 20 yards or so to his right to cut that off
nips back in after pitching on length around off stump, defended towards the off side
shuffles across to whip that one to deep square leg
veers in towards middle and leg, he drops it towards midwicket with soft hands for a quick single
low full toss, but Smith fails to take full toll of that as he drives it straight to mid-on. Looked like he wanted to work it into the gap between mid-on and midwicket
accurate start, full on off stump, played back down the pitch
angles one back in from wide of the crease, patted back to the bowler
opens the bat face late to use the pace and run it down to third man
looks to force one through the off side, gets a thick inside edge that rolls back down the pitch
punched on the up, but straight to backward point
punched again, but will get just a single as the cover fielder moves swiftly to his left to stop that
drawn forward, but can only get a thick edge. Doesn't matter though as it races past the vacant slip cordon. Third man was too square. Finch jabbed at that, but is lucky this time
hint of extra bounce from length area outside off, bunted to point
defended to the left of Holder, wants the single thinking he'd hit it to mid-off but quickly realised that wasn't the case
gets on top of the bounce and pats it back to the bowler
floats it full on off stump, Finch gets a good stride forward and then offers a dead bat to defend
hustled for pace, and so he isn't entirely in control of the pull, gets a top edge that falls short of fine leg

he goes wide of the crease and angles this full ball on off, Finch attacks it and lofts it cleanly over extra cover, KP runs to his right and right-boots the ball by the edge of the boundary. Carlos applauds KP's effort
cracked! Full on off, Finch plonks his front foot forward and belts it over the bowler's head. Nobody could stop that
full, off-stump line, dabbed to backward point
Finch uses the incoming angle and glides a single to fine leg
back of a length and outside off, skip Smith shuffles across, punching to point
back of a length on off, Smith shuffles across, this time punching to mid-on
starts off with a 107ks floaty incutter on middle, Finch waits and pokes it out in front of midwicket
another full offcutter, 110ks, whippy drive to long-on

KP strikes in his first over and nearly does a Tahir, again. He looks towards the stands, perhaps, and does the finger-on-the-lip celebration. The lack of pace does Finch in. Back of a length incutter, comes in from outside off at 115ks, Finch aims to force it from there. This means that he drags a catch to Samuels at deep midwicket
full and cuts in to rap the pad, not given by umpire Kettleborough, looked like it was heading down leg
full and wide outside off, Bailey chases and sends a bottom edge wide of reach of Ramdin. Beats the diving keeper to his left and rolls away to the fine leg fence
full on off, Bailey presses forward and blocks this roller back to KP
offbreak on off, not much turn, Smith shuffles across and whips to deep midwicket
full and breaks in quickly, defended back
full and breaks in again, poked in front of short leg
spinning into the legs, tucked.... KP intercepts it at short leg
Bailey hangs back and jabs it away past KP
whipped from off stump through square leg
short and wide outside off, chopped to point
offcutter short and outside off, whipped to midwicket
cutter outside off, forward and bunted to the covers
short and wide outside off again, Smith slashes a cut to backward point
pitched up on off, nudged into the covers for a single
back of a length and sticks in the surface outside off, Bailey waits and late-cuts to third man
Bailey plays back to this offbreak and whips to deep midwicket
slid down leg, Smith aims to shovel it fine, no dice, wide
full and straight, no turn, Smith twirls his wrists and puts it away to deep midwicket
length and breaks in, worked to short fine leg
nifty footwork and wristwork. Smith twinkles down to meet a full one outside off. He then whips it over short midwicket
Narine loses his rhythm. He fires it quick and short down leg, Smith just helps it squarer of short fine leg
tossed full on middle, picked away through midwicket
another little incutter on off, pushed back to KP
shortish incutter, sticks in the surface and climbs onto Smith, who cuts and chops an inside edge to short fine leg
Bailey whips a full one from off stump to short midwicket
short and comes in on off, Bailey camps back and clips to the right of short midwicket for one
looped outside off, forward and dabbed to short extra cover
pitched up and wide outside off, Smith reaches out, slicing a drive to third man
slides full on middle and leg, nudges and misses, as Narine hits the pad
Bailey steps out, Narine dragged his length back and found some turn to hit the pad again
Narine drops it short again, this is wide outside off. Bailey shifts his balance to the back foot and cracks a cut to the cover boundary
slower and fuller on middle, knocked to the midwicket region
short again on off, the batsman steps out and flays it straight to short extra cover
pushed through a bit short on middle, Bailey hangs back and forces a single to long-on

he goes wide of the crease and gets it to veer in sharply from outside off, strikes the pad in front of off and middle. Ump Kettleborough does not budge. Impact in line, yes. Going over the stumps? Oh, the tracker shows that it would have hit middle
full and angled in on off, defended back to the bowler
full and floated outside off, defended to the covers
full and angled in on middle, blocked out
full and aimed at off, Bailey blocks it to the covers
Bailey reaches out and pushes this full ball to point. He plays out a maiden
lobs a full toss on middle, squeezed back to the bowler
very full on middle, jabbed to sweeper cover for one
down the track and quietly defended to cover
Benn goes short and outside off, allows Bailey to rock back. Cut to short extra cover
drifts in on middle, Bailey answers with a straight bat and blocks

turn and bounce! Skirts past the outside edge of the groping bat. Drifts in on off and turns away late, Bailey had to play at it. He is beaten emphatically. This should encourage Benn, as well as Zampa. Ramdin takes it just below his chest
length and outside off, helped down to third man for one
inducker, Bailey plays back and squirts an inside snick onto the pad
full and angled in at off, Bailey closes the bat-face and defends to the midwicket region
Carlos pulls his length back on off, Bailey hops and stabs to short extra cover
yikes! This indipper kept low and outside off, beats the inside edge. Bailey reaches out, cuts and misses
Good variation. Carlos drags this shorter and offers not much width outside off, Bailey responds by getting on top of the bounce and punching to short extra cover
tossed on off, dropped into the covers for one
forced past short extra cover for one as Bailey gets a run, after playing out 15 dots
down the track and driven to long-on
now it's Bailey's turn to dance out and milk it down the ground, for two
pushed to short extra cover, straight to the fielder
drifts in and strays into the thigh, Bailey goes back and does not connect with the flick
whipped around the corner to deep square leg
length and outside off, forward and bunted to short extra cover
shorter and outside off, Bailey aims to pull. Ends up dragging a single to deep midwicket
sharp incutter, Smith seeks to cut, the ball does not come on. He chops an inside edge that whistles past the leg stump
back of a length and outside off, Bailey waits, waits, waits, and glides it to third man
short and outside off, Bailey rides it down to third man
drift back in followed by sharp turn, Bailey is beaten in flight as he skips out, blocks it somehow in the end
cuts but can't find the gap as he hits it straight to point, almost a mix-up but no damage done as Smith scampers through
steps out and works it across the line towards deep midwicket, Johnson Charles was caught napping
backs away, uses the width and cuts it to deep point
driven inside-out to sweeper cover, much better from the Smiling George
once again, hint of width is enough for Smith to work the ball into the gap towards deep point and come back for the second

got him! Bailey was just starting to tick over, but the slightest of mistakes has cost him. Brathwaite bowls an incoming length ball which Bailey looks to run it down to third man, but there wasn't much room to work with as he ends up chopping it back onto the stumps. The squeeze was on, you got the feeling that Bailey was getting a little edgy to score after a string of dots early on in his innings, but that isn't to be tonight.
shows the full face of the bat to defend
gets half-forward and defends again
straightens off length outside off, bunted to point
solidly behind the line again as he defends to the off side, Brathwaite isn't giving anything away either
drives, but plays outside the line and gets an inside edge that rolls back to the bowler. Wicket maiden
touch short, he makes room and crunches it to deep point

And he nearly had him with a beauuuuuty!! This one drifts back in from around the stumps, hits something and then turns square to beat Marsh's outside edge by a whisker. Benn thought there was an edge, but there wasn't here. Anyway, it didn't matter as Ramdin didn't collect it cleanly
quicker one on middle, gets back to defend
this one straightens from middle, he gets back to work it across the line but is late on the shot
opens the face of the bat to ease it wide of point for an easy single
gets a leading edge that rolls towards mid-off
driven on the up, and that has raced away into the cover boundary at the rate of knots. Too much width, Marsh frees his arms to belt that on the up!
uppish, but the edge falls safely into no man's land, third man comes around to stop that. Marsh on 999
gets across to defend gently to the off side
floats that full on off stump, Smith shuffles across and taps it to cover
worked off his pads into the gap at deep midwicket, wanted the second but the throw was a quick one at the bowler's end

dabbed with soft hands towards point, but he really had to scamper through to complete the run as he was pushed onto the backfoot, which meant he had an extra yard or two to make up. No damage done in the end as there was no direct hit
lovely flight, lands it on middle, driven with the spin with hard hands to cover
worked across the line to long-on
short, he gets back, makes room and cuts it, but straight to cover
too full this time, Smith gives it a proper thump that is half-stopped by Darren Bravo at cover
lunges forward and smothers the spin
slow turn from outside off, crunched to deep cover
width on offer, he gets on top of the bounce and cuts it behind point. No chance for third man. Not an auspicious start from Gabriel
hits the deck hard and gets some lift, Marsh is well inside the crease as he bunts it to the off side
width on offer, Marsh shapes to play a square drive but can't reach the delivery, easy call for the umpire
mistimed drive but he'll get a one, sweeper cover comes in to cut that off

too full, in the slot for Smith to lean forward, open the bat face and slice that into the gap behind point. Sweeper cover fielder Johnson Charles tried hard, but couldn't get across in time. Such was the timing on the stroke.
eased down to third man for an easy single
too short, Marsh mistimes an attempted cut to cover
gets forward and plays it with the spin to cover
chops it between cover and point for a quick single

not all that short, but Marsh still manages to find the gap behind point. Quality stroke. There was just a hint of width, and Marsh converted an inch into an acre. Played it really late and picked the gap to perfection
gets forward and bunts it back down the pitch
gets half-forward to ease that quicker one to the off side
driven with the spin to deep cover
plants his frontfoot forward and eases that on the up to deep cover

Christmas has come early for Gabriel after what was a horror spell until now. Rang long hop this one - too short - and Smith tries to fetch the pull from outside off when he could have easily looked to cut that behind point, gets a top edge and Marlon Samuels gleefully accepts the dolly at midwicket. Smith knew he was dead the moment he hit that. A hint of extra bounce on this surface also played its part.
this one's nice and full outside off, watched through to the keeper
flew off an open blade to point, good work there

edged, but safe! Doesn't carry to Ramdin, who spontaneously moved to his left. The ball was dying on him though as it races away off the deflection into the third man boundary. Can't blame Ramdin there. Maxwell looked to run that down a lot squarer. Lucky break

another one bites the dust. Gabriel didn't celebrate Smith's wicket, but that isn't the case now as he roars in delight. This one's an incoming length ball that nips back in a touch from the off stump, Maxwell misses the line completely and is struck plumb in front of leg stump Possibly a big moment in the match!
slow turn back into middle and leg, Marsh is struck high on the pad as he looks to work it to the on side
turned with the spin to short midwicket
touch fuller on middle, worked off the backfoot to deep midwicket
beaten on the drive. He plays for the turn but the ball skids straight on, well stopped by Ramdin
didn't pick the straighter one that drift back into middle and leg to hit him high on the pad
played off the backfoot to long-on. Eventful over
full and aimed at off, pushed back to Gabriel
even fuller on off, driven firmly to mid-off
pitched up and on off, sort of stops on Marsh. He is through with the lofted drive. Ends up chipping it over mid-off. The ball rolls away for four
full and straight, whipped to mid-on
full ball at off, Wade shuffles across off and clips it to midwicket
good length and angled in on off at 143ks, defended back to Gabriel
lobbed up on off, Wade defends to silly point
may have been a knuckle ball, curls in, Wade smothers it to the leg side
Wade pre-meditates a sweep, Narine alters his length and pushes full outside off. Wade adjusts and drives to the covers
a touch shorter, punched to the covers
loopier on middle, Wade bends forward in defence
round-armish full ball on middle, Wade keeps it out and rounds off a maiden
slides outside off with extra bounce, defeats the attempted cut. Bounces into the gloves of Ramdin
pushed through on off, defended
length ball on middle, half-forward and pushes to short extra cover
shorter and drifts in to cramp Marsh for room, mis-timed into short extra cover
tossed full on off, driven down to long-off to break the sequence of 11 dots
dangled up full and outside off, not much turn, Wade stretches forward for a sweep across the line and only meets with thin air
whipped off the pads through midwicket
dropped short and outside off, stands tall and punches to the covers
darted outside off, Wade cuts and rolls an outside edge behind point for three
slid through short on off, camps back and pushes to mid-on
offbreak on off, fraction short, punched to long-on off the back foot
slider on middle, Wade aimed to back away and is cramped for room. Kept out
full and drifts in, stabbed to the covers
arm-ball, snakes in, chopped back off an inside edge
short and turns away outside off, forced to sweeper cover
back of a length and turns in, nudged towards square leg

Chopped on! The bails are sent flying. Having gone wicketless on Friday, Benn nips out Marsh. Pushed through quicker, 90.4ks, and turns away from the right hander. He has a lazy waft away from the body after stepping back and chops it onto the stumps via an inside edge. The WI fans are dancing and grooving in the stands
Benn greets Starc with a yorker, he drops his bat down in time and survives
Wade bends and pre-mediates a sweep, hit from off stump to short fine leg
offbreak outside off, left alone
slider on off, punched to mid-off
tossed full on off, Starc winds up for a swipe and ends up skying it straighter for four
knuckle ball, Narine special, whipped to long-on
full knuckle ball, Wade drives and squirts an inside edge behind square
tossed outside off, dabbed to point
Wade picks it from the off stump and sweeps a single to fine leg
tossed up and drifts in, poked to the covers off an inside edge
fired into the leg stump, cramps Starc, deflected to short fine leg
flighted and spins in, forward and pushed back to Benn
Wade leans back and square-cuts this short ball from outside off to the point fence. Australia need more of this
round-arm full ball outside off, carved off the back foot to short third man, where Fletcher fumbles. Lazy to bend down and collect the ball
knuckle ball slides in, played back to the bowler
floater on off, Starc has a big swing at it and toe-ends it...... It drops in front of wide long-off. Charles din't quite attack the ball
tossed on middle, Wade stretches forward and paddles to short fine leg
kncukle ball drifting down leg, tickled to short fine leg, where Gabriel makes a diving save, and takes some pace off the ball
leg-side wide
looped up full on middle, dead-batted
shortish on off, camps back and defends
dipping full toss on the leg stump, misses the flick and takes it on the pad
fired down leg, wide
speared outside off, Starc aims for a slog sweep and is beaten, as is Ramdin
short and spins in, cramping Wade. He shapes to pull and ends up flapping it ungainly over midwicket
straighter one, which is pushed down to long-off
Benn liberally tosses this up outside off, Wade presses forward and eases a single to long-off
very full on middle, driven through the covers for a couple
Wade pre-meditates a sweep, floater on off, he intended to go finer. Ends up hitting the ball through square leg
pushed through, round-arm action, chopped to the off side
Narine lobs this offbreak outside off, Starc has a mighty mow across the line. Slog sweep and a miss
full and straight, stabbed through the covers
he whirls down a quicker straighter one outside off. Zips past the outside edge
lifter angled away outside off, Wade drops his gloves on it and sways his upper body out of the way
back of a length on middle, Wade uses his wrists and manipulates it towards the short midwicket region. A clean grab and a throw from Holder could have had Wadea
awaycutter outside off, short, slapped to point
length ball on leg stump, heaved to fine leg
rushing short ball on off, pulled to deep midwicket
yorker veers in, Starc drops his bat down and toe-ends it behind square
cuts, but finds point
fires it wide outside off, Starc shapes to cut but can't reach the delivery
as clean as it can get! Chips down the track, gets to the pitch and swings across the line. Excellent use of the bottom hand to get the elevation, and that flew into the crowd at deep midwicket. Wow
mistimes a cut again, straight to point

first wicket for Narine, he has his revenge this time. Nothing wrong with the legality of the delivery. He tosses it up generously, the ball spins away sharply and beats Starc's wild swing. In trying to slog again, Starc was outside the crease as Ramdin collected the ball cleanly and whipped the bails off in a jiffy, with the backfoot a good couple of yards out.
cleverly done! Gets back into the crease, opens the bat face and plays it really late, past short third man. Super touch, super timing
drifts into middle, driven down to long-on. End of Narine's spell
too full, but well down leg. Wade misses a faint tickle, Holder will have to bowl that one again
pulled well, that's a top shot! Gets on top of the bounce and helps it behind deep backward square. Bisected the gap to perfection
cuts, but straight to short third man. A metre on either side and it was four
angles a yorker-length delivery across Wade, who squeezes it wide of the keeper for a quick single
chops that down to third man for an easy single
goes for a full-blooded drive, gets a thick inside-edge that rolls to long-off, called for two but that was clearly a case of sheer optimism
full toss on the pads, worked behind square on the leg side, they thought about the second briefly before giving up the idea
angles a slower one into the pads from wide of the crease, he chips it over the infield to the man coming in from deep midwicket
slower one again, slapped to Charles at long-off

easy pickings for NCN! Fine leg and third man were up, which meant Pollard couldn't really drift too much on either side. This one's a juicy half-volley on the pads, which he clips past short fine leg

How did Ramdin miss the stumps from a couple of yards? I really don't know. Coulter-Nile squeezes a yorker behind the stumps and takes off, Ramdin does the difficult job of running in and then picks the ball up with one hand and fires an underarm throw which misses the stumps by a long way. The batsman was nowhere in the picture
floats the slower ball down leg, easy call
works it back past the bowler to mid-off

catching opportunity, but no one takes it. He looked to swing, got it high in the air but the ball fell in no man's land even as two fielders came running in from the leg side boundary - one from deep midwicket and another from deep square leg
angles a full-length delivery outside off, Wade fails to get some bat on it
walks across to paddle, gets it high on the pad and only a run will result as short fine leg stops it
makes some room to swing over midwicket, gets a thick inside edge towards deep square, aggressive running gives them the second
backs away to carve one over point, but Holder did well by bowling it full and wide outside off, NCN could only watch it through to the keeper in the end

swung in the air, this goes miles in the air, Bravo settles underneath that at mid-on and takes the skier without much fuss. Coulter-Nile went across the line even as the bat face turned in his hand, which meant there wasn't much power generated behind the stroke. Easy as they come for Bravo
drives, but gets it high on the bat, stopped by cover
slow off-cutter that has been bunted wide of point to bring Wade back on strike
swung across the line, doesn't time it well, long-on comes in to cut that off
into the blockhole from wide of the crease, Zampa squeezes it wide of point for another quick single
clean strike, what a beauty! This one was full and angling across, Wade swung across the line and saw that sail over long-on. Boom!
drills one down to long-on, wanted the second but he hit it too well

beaten by the slower one. Cany variations again, rolls his fingers over the ball and lands it just around off stump, Zampa was through with the stroke even before the ball arrived and missed. Not far away from the stumps
terrible delivery, high full toss but well outside off. Wade can't reach

wow, he's hit that superbly. This one was full and angling across, Wade once again went cross-batted across the line, and Wade used his bottom hand to swing across the line and hammer it over deep midwicket
driven to the man at the edge of the circle at cover, gem of an innings from Wade under the circumstances
dabbed back to the bowler, some lift off the deck from the length area on off stump on that occasion
clean strike over cover, but there's a sweeper circling around the ropes to keep it down to just two
slapped down the ground, straight to long-on
yorker-length ball angling away, swung across the line, he manages to squeeze it to deep midwicket
low full toss outside off, Wade reaches out to squeeze it into the gap at deep point
down on one knee as he makes room and crashes it into the gap between long off and deep cover, super knock this. 8th ODI fifty
too full and well outside off, umpire Joe Wilson thinks it was well inside the wide line. Wade isn't impressed. Poor decision

swung across the line, Wade gets a thick inside edge to Brathwaite's left. Zampa took off for the run without realising the bowler moved to his left. Then it was a battle between the two, and Brathwaite runs all the way to the stumps to remove the bails at the non-striker's end. Zampa was a couple of yards short of the crease
swing and a miss. Looked to drag the slog from well outside off towards cow corner. Excellent call by the umpire this time
what a hit to finish the innings. Too full, he gets down on one knee, gets underneath the ball and swings that across the line over wide long-on. Super hit!
full-blooded swing back in from outside off, beats Fletcher's drive as the ball nearly shaves the inside edge. Wow, what a start
invites the drive by bowling it full outside off, moves back in a touch, left alone
loaded with risk, but he's off the mark. The ball swerves back in to take a thick inside edge that flies past square leg. Had he missed it, he would have been walking back to the dressing room
gets half-forward and eases that one to gully
floats it full and across Fletcher who pats it back down the pitch
wrong line, on the seventh stump outside off, will have to re-bowl that
good carry from the length area outside off, left alone
starts off accurately, with a back of length delivery outside off, bunted to the off side
too straight, flicked to square leg
slashes, and gets the boundary. There was width, Charles ensured there were no half measures and sliced it over backward point. Third man had no chance
on middle and leg, he hops back and helps it down to fine leg, where Khawaja effects a tumbling stop
floats it full and around off stump, Charles is caught in two minds, lets it go in the end
again on the pads, eased to long leg, easily done
Zampa at square leg took the pace off that flick shot, Starc was too full and drifting into the pads, neat flick from Charles
floats it full and well outside off, another wide. Starc is looking to cause confusion in the batsman's mind perhaps by floating one across after getting a couple of deliveries in
crisp drive, but Bailey dives to his right to stop that at cover point

just eludes the outstretched hands of Smith at second slip. Can't call it a chance really. This was full, Charles went after that one, but the ball kept going away from the skipper. Third man stops it. Can't call it a chance
angled full and across the batsman, who watches it go
beaten on the drive. Minimal feet movement as he shapes to play the cover drive. Starc has a few words for Fletcher
nips away off the seam as Starc angles it across Fletcher, left alone
hit high on the thigh pad as he looks to whip it off his hip
pushed back to the bowler off the backfoot
once again some lift off the deck from the length area, Charles hops back to tuck that away but is hit on the thigh pad
shapes to cut, bottom edges it to the off side
cut away off the frontfoot but straight to backward point
looks to work it across the line but the length ball nips back in to hit Charles on his back pad as it rolls to Wade
covers the line of that full ball as he defends to the man coming in from point
full but well outside off, exercise for the umpire
hops back and bunts it gently to point
appeal for lbw. This one bends back in a shade to hit Fletcher on the pad. Was there an inside edge? Yes, clearly. Steven Smith got that right too as he prevented Starc from going for a review
beaten on the drive again. This was too full, and he was late on the stroke
driven wide of cover for an easy single
squeezed behind point, third man is square so one it will be
skiddy short ball on the off stump, the batsman is late on the pull and is rapped on the flap of the pad
fraction short on off again, short-arm pulled away to fine leg
back of a length and angled in, short-armed away to square leg, where Zampa makes a tumbling save to his right
similar ball, the batsman swivels on the back foot and pulls it fairly wide of Zampa, Khawaja mops it up at deep backward square leg
banged in shorter on off, cramping Charles. Pushed back to NCN
keeps it short, this is outside off, the batsman hangs back, running a single down to third man
very full and angled in, driven to mid-on
back of a length, veers in, beats the flick and pings the pad
back of a length at the off stump, Charles lays into it, muscling a swipe over square leg for six
stands up tall to a back of a length ball on off. Punched to mid-off
back of a length on off, another firm straight-bat punch to mid-off ensues
short and width outside off, Charles latches onto it, unleashes a rasping cut to the point boundary
NCN hits the deck hard, short on off, fended into the pitch
full on off, tight stuff, clipped to mid-on
back of a length and bounces over the off stump, Fletcher loses his patience. He wants to bash it across the line over midwicket. Beaten!
back of a length on off, Fletcher sits back, drops it to short extra cover, and sets off
back of a length on off, dabbed away to point
short, cramps the batsman for room, on off, turned to mid-on for another urgent single
length and outside off, no movement, Charles just punches through the line as the ball purrs away to the cover boundary
lifting delivery outside off, Charles leaves it be
shorter on off, punchily blocked to short extra cover
full on off, he looks to hit through the line again. Ends up miscuing a drive to mid-off
short on off, sits back and whips through square leg
short and outside off, gets on top of the bounce, playing to point
Charles continues to prosper. He flies down the track, the bowler pulls his length back. Swiped to the midwicket fence
turned to deep square leg
short and hurled on off, punched back to the bowler
short and veers in on off, cramped for space. The batsman fends to midwicket
short and just outside off, slapped out to point
Fletcher finds his release. Overpitched and outside off, Fletcher slots a drive through the covers. Drilled away with authority
back of a length on off, presses forward and defends back to the bowler
similar length but the line is wider outside off, helped down to third man

Here comes Fletcher, down the track.... Here goes Fletcher. The opener's miserable stay ends. This is an easier chance for the Australian captain. Fletcher, perhaps, showed his ace early by galloping out. Hazlewood shortened his length on off and found some extra bounce. Takes the edge near the higher part of the bat and carries to slip. Overhead catch
back of a length on off, defended to the covers
rising short ball on off, Bravo rides the bounce and plays towards the covers
good length and angled across off, nudged to midwicket
dug in outside off from over the wicket, Bravo shapes to pull and miscues it to mid-on
short and outside off, Bravo leaps, rises on top of the bounce and crisply punches to the covers
full and angled across the left hander, left alone
full on middle, a punchy drive to mid-off ensues
similar ball, ignored outside off
pitched up and angled across, Marsh builds the pressure further with a maiden. Left alone
NCN hurls it short on off, Charles gets on top of the bounce and blocks
pitched up on off, pushed to mid-on
short and wide outside off, lashes a cut and finds point
length ball on off, clipped to mid-on
Back of a length and sits up outside off, Bravo stays back and executes a wristy pull to the left of mid-on, through midwicket for four. Stylishly done!
NCN retorts with a bouncer, angled across the left-hander, Bravo sways his upper body out of the way and lets it pass over to the keeper
short one on off, bursts off the surface en route to Wade as Charles hooks and misses. The ball whistles over the helmet. Not wided. Tight call. One bouncer for the over, says the square-leg umpire
glanced to fine leg for one
pitched up and angled away outside off, left alone
short on off, worked to square leg
Marsh comes from round the stumps and pushes it full and outside off, left alone
full and angled in just a shade outside off, more leaving action from Bravo
short and angled in, raps the batsman high on the bat. Mis-timed pull flaps to midwicket
good length and outside off, slapped through the covers for one
incoming ball, draws the inside edge as the batsman wafts. The ball rolls to square leg
nice and full on middle, neatly pushed with a straight bat to mid-off
back of a length and slants away outside off, passing the outside edge of the groping bat. Bravo was opened up a touch
too full and outside off, drives to mid-off
dipping full toss outside leg, wide
yorker, angled in, squeezed out
shorter legbreak, sits back and punches to short extra cover
floated on middle, Charles hangs back and drops it in front of his feet
too full on middle and leg, whipped to short midwicket
tossed on off, opens the bat-face and runs it to short third man
dropped short on off, Charles sits back and forces a single to long-on
drifting into the pads, worked to fine leg

runs were coming in a trickle, and the pressure has got to Bravo. Marsh angles a short of length delivery back in from around the stumps, Bravo is cramped for room as he looks to run it down to third man, and can only manage a faint nick through to Matthew Wade. Straightforward decision for the umpire, but Bravo started to walk even before he raised the finger. Trouble for West Indies
woah! Rip roaring bouncer first up, Samuels sights that late, perhaps, as he ducks underneath that one. Somehow manages to avoid it
another short ball on off stump, Samuels drops his wrists, arches back and lets that go
uses the pace to run it down to third man for an easy single
a slower one this time, Charles waits inside the crease and bunts it to the off side
beautiful shot! Played it literally off Wade's gloves. Rocks back, waits for the turn and plays it late to pick the gap behind point. Super stuff.
lunges forward to offer a dead bat
drifting into middle and leg, tapped to the leg side for a quick single, Samuels had to hurry, which he did
good work to stop that off his own bowling by diving to his left
driven with the spin to extra cover
quicker delivery, there's some rip off the surface, punched to cover

soft dismissal, Mitch Marsh has another. Failure again for Samuels! This one's a slower delivery on the stumps, there's a hint of grip off the surface, it cuts away a touch as well, Samuels gets a leading edge to Bailey at short cover as he closes the bat face early. Real trouble now for the hosts
cross-seam delivery at length outside off, left alone
this is full and tails back in from wide of the crease, Ramdin is late on a forward defensive stroke, but negotiates it in the end
oversteps in his quest for extra pace, this one's another good bouncer otherwise. Ramdin drops his gloves as he sees that through to the keeper. Free hit coming up
can't take toll of that. Banged in short at a healthy pace, Ramdin shapes to pull but is late on it, through to the keeper
grip off the deck, a cross-seam delivery again on off stump, Ramdin checks his shot as he pushes a touch early
waits inside the crease and bunts that to the off side
driven back to the bowler, who moves swiftly to his right to stop that
flatter one on off, driven with the spin to extra cover
tossed up on middle, Ramdin gets under the flight and drives, but straight to cover
too late to get down on that one which drifts back into middle and leg, hit on the pad
makes room and cuts it to deep point
the wrong' un this time, Charles shapes to cut but makes a quick adjustment and dabs it in the end to short third man

third one for Mitch Marsh. Johnson Charles is plays all around a straight delivery angled in to middle and leg and is plumb in front. Errs in judgment and has to walk back. For a moment, Charles thought about the review, but it would have been a futile exercise. The wheels are coming off West Indies' chase here.
Pollard had decided even before the ball was delivered that he would leave, the lift off the deck means the ball thuds into the bottom of his blade as he lets it go
yorker-length delivery outside off, Pollard is late on the stroke as he looks to run it down to third man
shapes back into middle, Pollard gets across and defends
shapes away off the seam from the length area on off stump, Pollard is squared up but defends that to the off side
neat roll of the wrists to flick that into the gap at deep midwicket
crunches the drive, but straight to extra cover
too short, he cuts, but finds cover again. Pressure building
another backfoot punch, Bailey at cover is in business again
drifts this into middle from wide of the crease, this time Ramdin finally manages to punch that to the left of cover for a single
hammered that off the backfoot, but there's sweeper cover to cut that off. Singles won't really help, West Indies need a release. Wonder where that's going to come from
driven inside-out to long-off as they amble through
another short ball, this is getting a little predictable now, Ramdin sways out of the way
back of length delivery outside off, watches it through to the keeper
stabs forward, gets it off the outer half of the bat, ball rolls to the left of cover as they sneak through for a run
gets a good stride forward and defends
gets on top of the bounce and bunts it back down the pitch
slashes but is late on the stroke. Scoring opportunity missed again. There was enough width on offer, point was inside and it would have been four had he hit it over the infield
edged and the ball flies into the third man boundary. Too short, Ramdin shapes to cut and gets a thick edge. Really, that's the only way a boundary was coming at the moment
driven with the spin to the cover fielder
cuts, and cuts well. Deep point fielder in business
keeps low as the ball spins away from middle, Pollard wrists it into the gap at deep square leg, good running
slow turn, there's plenty of grip and bounce as Pollard takes his bottom hand off the grip as he defends
muscles the pull over midwicket, Nathan Coulter-Nile does well to run around the ropes and stop that
struck on the pad by an incoming delivery that keeps low. Starc appeals, but he knew Ramdin was saved by an inside edge there
on the pads, worked towards deep square leg

appeal for lbw as Pollard stabs outside the line of the stumps, that's what the umpire is indicating as well. Smith was about to review that until he saw the umpire agree with his suggestion. There was an inside edge too, and a big one at that
full toss tailing in, pushed to mid-off
pushes outside the line of the ball, gets an inside edge onto the pad again
squeezed to backward point, Maxwell cuts that of
draws him forward with flight, Ramdin blocks with a dead bat
drills a low full toss to long-off
in the slot, and boom! Gets to the pitch of that in-drifter and lofts him over the bowler's head, bisects long-on and long-off
quicker one on middle and leg, defended to the leg side

flat hit that would have taken the long-on fielder with it. Too short, Pollard rocks back and flat-bats the pull. Coulter-Nile threw himself in the air to take that one-handed but the ball kept travelling
slow turn away from off stump, eased to the off side
Starc goes wide of the crease and angles it in, Ramdin gets his front leg across, his head falls over. Ungainly. Pinged on the pad
speared in, cramps Pollard for room, kept out
yorker on off, swerves in, Pollard whips and toe-ends to deep midwicket
strays on the hips, tucked uppishly to fine leg
goes too full and outside off, Ramdin reaches out and is left searching for a drive. Slices it through point
leg-stumpish ball, deflected behind square

Pollard tries to clear long-off. Instead, he finds the fielder. Zamps loops this legbreak outside off, and draws the big hit from KP. He goes with the turn and slices a lofted hit to Hazlewood, tumbling to his left at the edge of the boundary. Smart, smart catch. Hazlewood hung on even as the ball bobbled out
tossed on middle, Holder presses forward and blocks
Holder needs just two balls in match to get open his account. A touch overpitched and outside off, driven inside-out through the covers
Zampa gives this plenty of air on middle, defended
there comes a quicker one - a googly - stabbed through point for one
legbreak outside off, Ramdin watches it through to Wade
inswinging yorker, 143ks, dug out
full and outside off from round the wicket, left alone
low full toss outside off, carved to third man
back of a length and angled in, Ramdin camps back and blocks to the leg side
bouncer, angled in, 141ks, Starc has Ramdin ducking for cover
veers in full on off, clipped in front of square on the leg side
tossed and dips on middle, Ramdin check-drives and it does not carry to a diving Smith at short extra cover
pretty full on middle, pushed to long-off
straighter one on off, Holder plays for the legbreak and sends an outside edge to short third man
pushed fuller on middle, driven down the ground to long-off
nicely looped on off, driven past Zampa to long-off
fired straight on middle, hit back to the bowler
length ball on off, tapped back to the left-armer
yorker tails in on middle, jabbed out to midwicket
back of a length and angled in, Holder keeps back and defends to short extra cover
angled in full and swings away outside off, Holder chases it with a drive away from the body and misses
angled in and (reverse)swings away again, Holder drives and carves it in the air over backward point
147.3ks yorker outside off, the ball zips through even before Holder jammed his bat down
looped up and turns away outside off, Ramdin seeks to loft it. Instead, slices it in front of sweeper cover
flighted on middle, blocked off the front foot
shorter legbreak, Holder punches off the back foot to the fielder patrolling the cover fence
slower through the air on middle, Ramdin presses forward in defence
chopped from the stumps to deep cover
tossed on middle, no turn, nudged to short extra cover. Holder scampers across for a quick single
length and outside off, guided to third man
back of a length on off, Ramdin shuffles across and turns the ball to short midwicket
shortish on off, run to Maxi at backward point
bouncer, sharp one on middle, ducked under
full on middle, Ramdin works it to the leg side
full on off, Ramdin plays back, again, instead of pressing forward. Marsh draws an outside edge, which rolls to Maxi at backward point
flighted on middle, poked out to short extra cover
tosses a legbreak outside off, slices a drive and sends an outside edge... does not carry to Maxi
full on middle, blocked
Holder uses his feet, makes room, collapses his back leg and drives it inside out over extra cover. That hamstring seems to be fine
slides on off, defended
Zampa drops this short on off, slapped away to long-on
banged in and attacking the body, Holder shuffles across and works to midwicket
length on off, dabbed gently to backward point
full on middle, defended to short extra cover
short and outside off, slashed to sweeper cover
full and straight, clipped to right of short midwicket
back of a length and angled in, poked out to short midwicket
short and angled in, Holder hops, skips, and fends it back to the bowler
back of a length and outside off, Holder glides it past backward point. Some work for third man, running to his right
keeps it short and outside off, Holder is pushed back, tapping towards backward point
much fuller at off stump, wafty little drive to mid-on
short and angled in at off, Ramdin nearly topples over as he plays to short midwicket
good length on off, stops on Ramdin. He drives and stabs it back to the bowler, past the outstretched left hand of NCN. The bowler, actually, finger-tipped it away. Just did not stick into the hands
length on off, helped to third man

straight in line, dab-and-run single to short midwicket. Risky single completed even as Bailey swooped down on the ball and nailed a direct hit. Holder did well to slide his bat in, despite a hamstring issue
kicks up from a back of a length and outside off, Holder loosens his grip and runs it down to third man
full and wicket-to-wicket line, clipped to short midwicket
length on off, pushed to mid-off
lifter outside off, the batsman ducks and lets it pass over to Wade. Ump Wilson does not call a wide
short indipper, jabs and squirts an inside edge onto the pad
Holder shows some intent. He steps out and belts this length ball over mid-on for a flat six
back of a length on off, steered to Maxi at backward point
bumper shading outside leg, whizzes over the left shoulder of Holder. This is wided

Holder steps out again, the scoreboard pressure tells. He gives a catch to sweeper cover. Finch reverse-cups the ball over his head. Good length and outside off, Holder could only miscue the lofted hit
lifter on the leg stump, the new man half-ducks out of the way
back of a length and bounces over the leg stump, Carlos has a massive wipe across the line and misses. His feet went nowhere

Starc has lost it in the lights! He tries to cover it with his hands and does not attempt the catch at fine leg. Leg-stump ball, picked up in the air. Starc stretched his right hand and ended up covering his face as the ball bounces to the boundary
good length and outside off, waft and a miss
short and wide outside off, slashed to the off side
bang! Back of a length and outside off, Carlos backs away and smites it over mid-off

Starc attempts the catch now. He drops it at short fine leg. Fullish and just a shade outside off, Carlos lap-sweeps and scoops it in the air. Starc jumps and stretches his right hand. The ball grazes it and rolls over
short and outside off, chopped away, Maxi dives and stops the ball with one hand. Sprawling dive at backward point
cutter drifts down leg, wide
bouncer on the leg stump, Carlos hooks. Wade throws himself to his left and does not catch the ball. Was there a bit of glove, there?
guided to third man
short and outside off, arches back and ramps to third man
short on top of off, tapped to the covers for one
might have been a cutter outside off, yes it is. Carlos swings early and misses
back of a length on off, blocked to short extra cover
Carlossssss pings it over square leg for six! Back of a length and outside off, possibly a slower one, Carlos holds a stable base and baseball-swings it cleanly over the boundary. Sailed away!
back of a length on off, guided to short extra cover
short on middle, pulled away to deep midwicket
two is the call from Carlos as this is picked up and dispatched over midwicket
First boundary off Marsh's bowling Full and outside off, in the slot, Ramdin lofts it cleanly through the line over mid-off
Ramdin loses his shape now as he whip-pulls this short ball to short midwicket. Bailey misses a direct hit, Carlos dives at the non-striker's end. The ball skips away for overthrows
bouncer, sails over Ramdin, wide
dug in short and outside off, Ramdin has a slog and gets a bottom edge to the keeper
full and heading into the pads, flicked through backward square leg
short on off, cramps Ramdin, chopped through point
cleaned em' up! Back of a length on middle, Carlos winds up and aims to slug it across the line. He misses it and Hazlewood nails the top of middle and roars. Carlos gone and with it WI's hopes?
back of a length and outside off, beats the outside edge
back of a length on off, swiped to mid-on
full toss on middle, whipped away, Finch tumbles to his right from wide long-on, great commitment. He saves a couple of runs for Australia
short on off, Ramdin gets on top of the bounce and pulls to deep midwicket
back of a length and angled in from round the stumps, hit back to the bowler. Marsh got his hands to it, but the ball did not roll back onto the stumps. Ramdin had backed up a fair bit
Narine opens the bat-face and steers it to point
offbreak from Marsh, Narine comes down the track and slices over extra cover, beats long-off running to his right. Narine has come out swinging
Narine leans back and slashes this short ball through the covers
Marsh shortens his length as Ramdin dances out. Flat-batted back to the bowler
short and outside off, left alone
back of a length on middle, Narine slogs and ekes out an inside edge, which ricochets off the pad to Wade
The middle stump is tilted back. Hazlewood hastening WI's slide. Good length on middle, Ramdin backs away outside leg and does not touch it. Timbaaaah! He couldn't connect with a leg-side slog
full on middle, Hazlewood draws an outside edge, wanders away to third man
Narine connects with the leg-side slog. Full on middle, swiped over midwicket

Hazlewood can't cling onto the return catch! Good length on middle, Narine, having stepped outside leg, drills it back to the bowler. Hazlewood stuck his right hand out, but could only tip it over to long-off
Narine stands tall to meet this short ball outside off, punched to deep cover
inswinging yorker on middle, Narine pushes and sends an inside edge to the long leg boundary
Narine takes a trip outside leg, Starc fires it full and outside off. Narine can't reach out. Leaves it alone
back of a length and holds its line outside off, 146ks, left alone again
Starc hunts for another yorker, this is hurled on the leg stump, tickled fine past the diving Wade for four
full and straight, Narine hangs back and flicks to midwicket
gets a thick inside edge to mid-on, they scamper through for a single

he's picked the bones out of that, but couldn't have picked out the man better. Steven Smith at the edge of the circle at cover had a thunderbolt coming his way, but he held on to it. Narine cleared his front leg to clatter that, but to no avail. Australia one wicket away from the cup!
swings across the line, Gabriel gets an inside edge towards deep midwicket

has he made clean connection? For most parts, it was six, until Glenn Maxwell leapt high, kept his eyes on the ball and then pulled off a stunner while he was air borne. All along, he was mindful of the ropes behind him as he timed his jump to perfection. Five wickets for Hazlewood, Australia are winners of the tri-series
